        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 8:32AM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 831 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Tishomingo, moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tishomingo, Tushka, Milburn, Coleman, Fillmore, Boggy Depot Park,
Caney, Lehigh, Ravia, Wapanucka, and Atoka.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
